Two police officers have been arrested with 7.5 grammes of bhang in Samburu. The officers were driving in a private car from Moyale to Isiolo when they were captured. "The two include a recruit and his instructor at Kiganjo. They were intercepted at Archers Post roadblock," an officer who sought anonymity told the Star on phone. The officers said they had received intelligence report and erected the roadblock to nab the suspects. "We received an intelligence from an informer that a vehicle suspected to be ferrying bhang from Moyale was heading towards Isiolo direction along Moyale- Isiolo highway. The vehicle registration KAQ 746F make Toyota 110 was seized," he said. Click here for the latest political news